  "summary": "Yuzu informs the detective that she witnessed her Uncle Aoba walking toward her brother Kei's room after midnight the previous night. Although the corridor was dark and she only saw his profile, she remains certain of his identity. The detective expresses skepticism regarding the timing of this sighting, noting that Inaba is already dead. Overwhelmed by guilt, Yuzu wonders if she could have saved her brother had she checked his room sooner.\n\nIn a separate development, Wanli Hua presents Mutou with an ancient, fragile book she discovered inside a table at a church. The volume is bound with ropes and contains torn pages with text in both Latin and English. Mutou identifies the object as the \"Lecanova Book,\" an apocryphal gospel of the New Testament that focuses on the humanity of Jesus during his crucifixion. \n\nKanae observes that the book is similar to one her grandfather used to carry when visiting a location referred to as a \"jail,\" which Kanade suggests might be the \"gate of hell.\" Kanae recalls her grandfather wearing a black cloak and carrying a strange tree branch while appearing to perform a secret ritual. Reflecting on the investigation, Xiao Yan considers whether the first victim, Itou, might have been the murderer using a scapegoat, or if the killer is utilizing the discovered book. Mutou and Kaneko depart to investigate these emerging facts further.",
